So nobody does it?<p><pre><code>  $sum = int($max/2) * ($max+1));
  $sum += int(($max+1)/2) if ($max & 1);
</code></pre>
This is perl of course but it is exploiting the fact that the sum of integers is a sum of constants ($max + 1) with an additional term (the &#x27;middle&#x27; integer) if the top number is odd.
